author: Arc13

text: @GabeMorris I think I played this game at the right time. I hadn't played a retro-styled RPG in a while so it felt like a Breath of Fresh Air VII (sorry for the bad joke). I loved how you had 2 powerup choices every time a character leveled up and I really liked how dungeons had a set number of battles before you had the option to completely turn them off. Great humor too and references (town names mixing japanese and english RPG titles for example: Motherbound, Lufestopolis, etc.).
